What if someone buys your item and does not like it when they receive it?



								
								wikiHow Contributor							

If the return policy is marked as "Returns Accepted", the buyer can return it. Just let the seller know that you're not satisfied with it, and he/she will work it out for you to make sure you're happy with what you get. However, it's likely that you will have to pay for shipping to send the item back.

