How does eBay collect their money and how much are we paying for this service?



								
								wikiHow Contributor							

You normally get up to 50 free listings per month and pay 30 cents per listing for any additional ones, unless you want to add some upgrades to your listing. You also pay a final value fee for each item that successfully sells, which is usually 10% of the total price including shipping. All fees for the previous month are automatically withdrawn from your linked PayPal account (and thereby, your bank account) around the middle of the next month. See http://pages.ebay.com/help/sell/fees.html for more details on fees.

