Helpful 11









Do I have to accept a low bid?



Vieno 

Yes. An auction is a binding legal contract. If for example, you list a $500 Gucci handbag for a starting bid of 99¢ with no reserve, and the highest bid is 99¢, you have to ship that Gucci bag when the buyer pays you 99¢. So don't do that. Start the auction for the lowest price you will accept for the item. Do not count on the bids increasing to your desired price. Canceling sales because you didn't get the price you wanted is infuriating to buyers, and eBay has a very low tolerance for this practice.

Thanks!

Yes
No


Not Helpful 1
Helpful 3









What if the items I'm selling are antique China, what should I look out and be prepared for?



Vieno 

Think very carefully before you sell these items on any site that requires you to ship them. Packaging them so that not a single piece is broken during shipment requires skill, experience, and the right packing material, which can be expensive in and of itself. Fragile items are usually heavy, making shipping expensive. I would highly recommend that you try selling these items locally using a site like craigslist or letgo instead of eBay.

