How to sell to a product to a CEO - QuoraThis page may be out of date. Save your draft before refreshing this page.Submit any pending changes before refreshing this page. Hide this message.QuoraSign In Startup Product Management Advice and Strategy CEO Hiring Startup Sale Advice and Strategy Startup Marketing Advice Chief Executive Officers Product Management Sales Marketing Startup Advice and StrategyHow do I sell to a product to a CEO?I am working on a product that promotes team collaboration inside a company. We're exploring who is the best internal role to market and sell this product to and think it may be the company CEO. We are trying to weigh the pros and cons of targeting the c-level to sell our product, particularly the CEO.UpdateCancelPromoted by ShowpadDiscover how Showpad sales enablement can help your business.Sign up for a free Showpad trial account and make your sales team more successful with sales enablement.Free Trial at showpad.comAnswer Wiki4 Answers  Kevin LippsAnswered 115w agoDoing whatever is necessary to make it appealing to them. CEOs want a practical product that will help make their job easier, the company they work for, and a good way to increase profit, and to reduce the number of loss by using it. Many times you have to go to other people to sell a product to a business, so the CEO may not be the best choice. If your product is good, then the chances is a CEO or their affliates may come to you to buy it. It comes down to these steps:1. Broadcast your advantage.2. Fit into your customer's routine.3. Work right out of the box4. Make benefits easy to spot.5. Let customers try it out6. Attract the Right Audience7. Properly Manage Expectations8. Remove Barriers to Buy the product9. Drive Engagement & Investment10. Make it Easy to Buy11. Prove That It Works12. Personalize It  13. Provide the Necessary Support14. Show why you are better than Competitors15. Sponsor an Event to Market the Product16. Pull a PR Stunt17. Share the Load with Affiliate Marketing18. Build the Right Relationships19. Use various resources to market the product, such as social media, websites, publications, advertizing, etc.20. Hire the right Sales Team to Sale the Product for you. Use a commission based pay scale, as it is based on performance, and it cost you less if they are in effective, but it gives the good sales people the incentive to work harder, to sale the product. 21. Any other people to required to run the business, such as web designers, PR, customer support, etc. Make sure you pay a marketable rate, to get a good quality in employees. Low pay will decrease the chances of getting skilled employees, and how much there is a turn over within the company. How long, and how much you will need, is a matte of the size of the company.Sources:How to Sell a Product: 5 Ways to Sell ItselfSaaS Marketing Plan: 5 Ways to Get your App to Sell ItselfHow to Market a Brand New Producthttps://blog.kissmetrics.com/you...370 Views · 1 UpvotePromoted by HeapHeap is like Google Analytics, but it's made for SaaS apps.Heap automatically tracks every action (e.g. click, swipe, pageview) users take in your web app.Learn More at heapanalytics.comRelated QuestionsMore Answers BelowI manage a young startup company in the valley. My only employee is great, but he's also a new father. Which means leaving work between 6 and ...What is the best way to approach a big company CEO to sell my product?In a startup, does the CEO do most of the work?As a startup CEO, how do you decide whether to keep pushing on with a new startup or throw in the towel?What must CEOs do to avoid getting fired?  Saulo Marti, EntrepreneurAnswered 115w agoWhat do you mean sell a product? Do you mean a new product to your own CEO, so he signs off on it? Or do you mean that your product/service is typically for CEOs in General? What would be the profile of a CEO? In all honesty, I don't like the idea of a product being sold to a Job occupation. A role. There are MANY different CEOs. But obviously you might have one that applies to management so much that it is only for CEOs in general. Can you share more?182 Views · 1 Upvote  Kalpesh Patil, Business Developer I Connector I Thought Leader I Delivering Results I Empowering IndividualsAnswered 114w agoFirst thing first. 1. Prepare your "Questionnaire". It will help you to get useful information. 2. Try to find out their problems or challenges which impacting on his current business process.3. After discussion ask him about his expectations from solution 3. Most important pitch your product as a solution on problems faced by CEO.4. Show him benefits.149 ViewsView More AnswersRelated QuestionsWhy CEO just add features to software product, but not try to sell it?Marketing: How would you sell Coke to a Pepsi CEO?How do I sell Oriflame products?What does it feel like being the CEO of a startup?How do I sell this product?Should the Startup CEO focus on product or creating the selling value of the company?How do I find a CEO for my startup?What's the best way to learn how to sell?What are the most common lies told by startup CEOs?Which is easy to sell product or service?Related QuestionsI manage a young startup company in the valley. My only employee is great, but he's also a new father. Which means leaving work between 6 and ...What is the best way to approach a big company CEO to sell my product?In a startup, does the CEO do most of the work?As a startup CEO, how do you decide whether to keep pushing on with a new startup or throw in the towel?What must CEOs do to avoid getting fired?Why CEO just add features to software product, but not try to sell it?Marketing: How would you sell Coke to a Pepsi CEO?How do I sell Oriflame products?What does it feel like being the CEO of a startup?How do I sell this product?Sitemap:#ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZAbout · Careers · Privacy · Terms · Contact


